      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">3.1004</ph> Contract clauses.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d182e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d184e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Insert the clause at FAR <xref href="52.203-13.dita#FAR_52_203_13"
                        base="i1063504"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.203-13</xref>, Contractor
Code of Business Ethics and Conduct, in solicitations and contracts if
the value of the contract is expected to exceed <ph rev="FAC 2021-01 October 1, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-013?>$6 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 3.1004 by removing from paragraphs (a), (b)(1)(i), and (b)(3) “$5.5 million” and adding “$6 million” in their places, respectively.?></ph> and the
performance period is 120 days or more.</p>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d184e23" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d182e35" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d184e28" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Unless
the contract is for the acquisition of a commercial item or will
be performed entirely outside the United States, insert the clause
at FAR <xref href="52.203-14.dita#FAR_52_203_14"
                              base="i1063571"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.203-14</xref>, Display of
Hotline Poster(s), if-</p>
                     <ol id="d182e48" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d184e37" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> The contract exceeds <ph rev="FAC 2021-01 October 1, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-013?>$6 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 3.1004 by removing from paragraphs (a), (b)(1)(i), and (b)(3) “$5.5 million” and adding “$6 million” in their places, respectively.?></ph> or a lesser
amount established by the agency; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d184e47" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                           </p>
                           <ol id="d182e67" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d184e52" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph> The
agency has a fraud hotline poster; or</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d184e57" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph> The contract
is funded with disaster assistance funds.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d184e62" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> In paragraph
(b)(3) of the clause, the contracting officer shall-</p>
                     <ol id="d182e99" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d184e68" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Identify
the applicable posters; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d184e73" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Insert
the website link(s) or other contact information for obtaining the
agency and/or Department of Homeland Security poster.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d184e78" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> In paragraph
(d) of the clause, if the agency has established policies and procedures
for display of the OIG fraud hotline poster at a lesser amount,
the contracting officer shall replace “<ph rev="FAC 2021-01 October 1, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-013?>$6 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 3.1004 by removing from paragraphs (a), (b)(1)(i), and (b)(3) “$5.5 million” and adding “$6 million” in their places, respectively.?></ph>” with the
lesser amount that the agency has established.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
